    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-12-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-12-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="1142"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1142">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860d.24/54</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Finnish Minister</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Procopé</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="22" xml:id="d1142fn22">Acknowledged for the Secretary of State on
                        December 15, 1939, by the Counselor of the Department, R. Walton
                        Moore.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 3658</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-11">December 11,
                            1939</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I herewith have the honour to inform Your
                    Excellency that the Finnish Government is sending a purchasing Committee <pb
                        facs="1040" n="1028" xml:id="pg_1028"/> to the United States. The members of
                    this committee are Lieutenant General V. P. Nenonen, former Inspector of the
                    Finnish Artillery, and Mr. W. Wahlf ors, President of the Wärtsilä metal concern
                    in Finland. They are accompanied by one secretary. General Nenonen is not
                    visiting the United States in his capacity of officer, but only as a member of
                    the above mentioned committee. The purchases will mainly consist of implements
                    of war. The committee is expected to arrive in New York about the 20th of
                    December.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hj. J. Procopé</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
